  "event_preview": "Las Vegas Motor Speedway is a 1.500-mile (2.414 km) tri-oval intermediate speedway in Paradise, Nevada, sitting in the desert 15 miles northeast of the famous Strip. The track complex spans 1,200 acres and has hosted major racing events across multiple disciplines since opening in 1996. The 20-degree banking and long sweeping turns encourage a wide variety of racing lines, making tyre management across long green-flag runs and pit strategy the primary battleground. With clean air at a premium and the lap times sensitive to track temperature in the desert climate, the intermediate speedway rewards consistency and crew chief decision-making as much as raw pace. The all-time Cup Series qualifying record belongs to Kurt Busch — a 27.167 seconds (198.771 mph) set for Penske Racing in October 2014.",
